        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 30 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Aho, or near Blowing Rock, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Boone...
Blowing Rock...
Deep Gap...
Todd...
Blowing Rock In Caldwell County...
Darby...
and Rutherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
